title: For Sale/Trade:  Hitler Youth Knife
postcontent:
Up for sale or trade is a hitler youth knife in good used condition. Assembled from left over parts after the end of WWII. This HJ knife has the original nickel plated hilt with twin slab black checkered plastic grips held with two nickel rivets. 
Centered in the front grip is the HJ red, black, and silver insigne inset between the two rivets. blade is plain and shows wear from use. 

Blade is marked Germany on the front for export law and SM/1940 on the other side . The standard black scabbard does attract a magnet and has the metal insert to hold blade and has the dimple. I believe this to be an original scabbard just marked germany for the export law. Its identical in every way to my war time scabbards. Not the rolled lip ones like the reproduction ones had. Rivets are tight and snap and keeper in good shape. Has the leather washer as well. 

This is a nice example of the real HJ knives assembled from original parts after the war for sale to soldiers still stationed over in Germany and for export as well. I have a pristine SM/1940 knife identical to this one that my uncle bought while still stationed in germany after the war and brought home in 1947. Scabbard, knife everything is the same. So this is not one of the new cheap made reproductions you find for 20 dollars.

I've bought and sold these and know what they go for online on gunauction.com, ebay, gunbroker and other sites when they do come around. Not going to sell this for 20.00s

I'm selling for 175 that includes the shipping within the US, no shipping to hawaii. Or I'll trade within wisconsin for a mosin nagant rifle, carbine would be more desired but open to a long rifle as well. 

715 323 0646 call or text anytime.

Looking to sell/trade my GSG.  It was an impulse buy a while back, and I Never got to shooting it (b/c I didn't need it and I shouldn't have bought it) - until this past weekend, I took it to the range, and Oh My God was it frustrating.  I've never dealt with such a piece of shit in all my life.  I don't know if the gun wasn't cleaned well prior to me buying it, or if its the defective mags or the ammo (as ive read online GSGs have problematic mags and are finicky with certain types of ammo)  I was shooting CCI 22lr "quiet-22" 40gr.  

Here's what happened: I'd charge 1 round into the chamber on a full mag, shoot, then click click (a round wouldnt fire, as the gun was not auto loading the 2nd round as it should) so I'd have to charge it manually before it would shoot. and on top of that, much of the time when I was doing the manual charging, the rounds would get bent up and would fail to feed.  SUUUPPPPERRRR FRUSTRATING.  I gave up. and I couldn't even look at the thing, much less clean it upon arriving home from the range.

Someone please take this off my hands.  I do not want to even mess with it.  This is what I get for making an impulse buy without doing Any research.  Laughable, but I thought it "looked cool" so I figured what the hell, cheap ammo, should be fun.  Stupid mistake.

Not saying all GSG's are flawed, or that mine even is - I just know what I went through and I want Nothing to do with it ever again.

Please do not try and Kill me on this deal, as I'm willing to eat a bit of a loss obviously, but give me some credit for at least being upfront and honest.

Last thing I'd want to do to someone is dick them over with whatever problem I've inherited with this GSG.  Hopefully someone can figure out what the deal is and restore it to good working order.

Sorry for the length of the post, thanks for looking.

Just make me an offer.  I'll obviously consider cash.  Ammo (45, 40).  guns.  Would be willing to add cash towards intriguing deals.

Again I really dont think theres anything mechanically wrong with the gun, I think theres something small thats causing the problems, or its just the ammo straight up.  Either way, I do not want to go down the path of trying to figure it out.  I'd rather cut my loses and let someone else who knows more about rifles deal with it.

Thanks.

title: For Sale/Trade:  WWII German Youth Knife
postcontent:
I've got a youth knife in good used condition. Assembled from left over parts after the end of WWII. This HJ knife has the original nickel plated hilt with twin slab checkered plastic grips held with two nickel rivets. Centered in the front grip is the HJ red, black and silver insigne inset between the two rivets. Blade is plain and shows wear from use. But still in good shape. Has the leather washer. 

The blade is marked Germany on one side for the export law and SM/1940 on other side. The black scabbard is magnetic as originals are and this one is the same as the scabbards on my WWII issue knives. It has the liner inside and the dimple on front. No rolled stamped lip like the reproduction ones.  Also has germany stamped on it for the export law. Most of my italian carcano rifles have italy stamped on them in the same manner for export. And they are all WWII and pre WWII year dated recievers. 

Keeper and snap are in good shape, rivets on scabbard good as well. This is not a 20 dollar repro you get at a knife show or online. this is assembled from original parts and they were sold to soldiers still stationed in germany after the war and for export sales as well. My uncle gave me two youth daggers and one is an original pre war dated example and I have others in my collection. And he gave me a Sm/1940 just like this that he bought while still stationed over there after the war. 

I know what they sell for on auction sites, ebay and other places and not going to give it away and don't try and tell me its something its not. I know what it is and have done my research. I collect the originals and the ones made from original parts sold after the war ended. I have originals stamped with germany on them for export and paid alot of money for them. The germany is there because of the export law. 

715 323 0646 call or text and I'm selling for 165 that includes shipping. These Sm/1940's are getting harder to find anymore.

USGI and/or mil-spec.:
